## Dashboard Example Submission Checklist

Please verify that your contribution meets all requirements:

### Required Components

- [ ] Dashboard JSON file is included and properly formatted
- [ ] All supporting Jupyter notebooks are included (if applicable)
- [ ] Example-specific README.md is complete with all required sections
- [ ] Main dashboards README.md has been updated with example summary

### Documentation Quality

- [ ] Setup instructions have been tested and work correctly
- [ ] All dependencies are documented
- [ ] Dashboard variables and settings are documented
- [ ] Example follows the naming conventions

### Code Quality

- [ ] Code is well-commented and readable
- [ ] Notebooks are executable from top to bottom without errors
- [ ] All notebook cells include appropriate markdown documentation

### Security & Privacy

- [ ] No sensitive information (credentials, URLs, etc.) is included
- [ ] No environment-specific information (`workspaceId`, `productID`, etc.) is
      included

### General Requirements

- [ ] I have read and followed the
      [Dashboard Contributing Guidelines](../examples/dashboards/CONTRIBUTING.md)

---

**For Reviewers:** Please verify that the dashboard example is complete,
functional, and follows all contribution guidelines.
